<#
.SYNOPSIS
    This PowerShell script ensures a secure account lockout duration to prevent successful brute-force password attacks. 

.NOTES
    Author          : Andres Torres
    LinkedIn        : linkedin.com/in/andres-torres-richardson
    GitHub          : github.com/CyberTechTorres
    Date Created    : 2025-11-15
    Last Modified   : 2025-11-15
    Version         : 1.0
    CVEs            : N/A
    Plugin IDs      : N/A
    STIG-ID         : WN11-AC-000005

.TESTED ON
    Date(s) Tested  : 2025-11-15
    Tested By       : Andres Torres 
    Systems Tested  : "STIG-Andres"
    PowerShell Ver. : 5.1.26100.7019

.USAGE
    Put any usage instructions here.
    Example syntax:
    PS C:\> .\STIG-WN11-AC-000005.ps1 
#>

# Sets the Account Lockout Duration to 15 minutes or greater. 0 requiring an administrator to unlock the account which is more restrictive.
$duration = 15  # Set this to 15 or higher to meet STIG compliance
net accounts /lockoutduration:$duration

# Optional: Verify current settings
net accounts
